<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - HEATED
        MIRRORS WITH POWER MIRRORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>HEATED MIRRORS WITH POWER MIRRORS</title>
        <table id="t0823205" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Heated Mirrors With Power Mirrors</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.83in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F34 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Fuse F34.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition and correct. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F34, measure voltage from 14N to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F34, 14N to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 14N or 14P and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (111) and measure voltage from 78L to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(111), 78L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78L and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (111) measure voltage from 78L to 78-GF.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(111), 78L to 78-GF.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in ground circuits 78-GF, 78-GB or 78-GA and repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Attach jumper wire across power mirror switch (111) terminals that were connected to
                                circuits 78K and 78J. Measure resistance between sw. terminals that were connected to
                                78L and 78GF, while moving the sw. to the up and down position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Switch term. at 78L and 78GF.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm each direction.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace power mirror switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Install jumper wire between 78L and 78K. Turn key sw. on. Disconnect conn. (113) and
                                measure voltage from 78K to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(113), 78K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78K and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Install jumper wire between 78-GF and 78J. At conn. (113), measure resistance of
                                circuit 78J to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(113), 78J to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78J and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumpers and reconnect conn. (111) and (113). Does power mirror motor operate
                                with switch in up or down position?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Mirror circuitry checks good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>For heated mirror diagnostics, refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s08230_33.xml" xrefid="x0823201">Heated Mirrors.</hotlnk>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
